<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANC Welcomes Annoucement of State of Emergency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANC Welcomes Annoucement of State of Emergency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103094794 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0928 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB3103094794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg March 31 SAPA -- The African National 
Congress on Thursday [31 March] said it welcomed the 
announcement of a state of emergency in kwaZulu as long as it 
allowed free and fair political activity in the area, ANC 
spokesman Carl Niehaus told SAPA soon after the announcement by 
President F.W. de Klerk. 
  He said the ANC, as a member of the Transitional Executive 
Council [TEC], called on Wednesday for a state of emergency 
"because of the very serious situation that prevails in Natal". 
  "The ANC therefore welcomes the announcement by Mr de Klerk 
that a state of emergency is introduced in Natal/kwaZulu. 
  "We fully support the state of emergency as long as it 
allows 
full freedom of political activity and full freedom to hold 
political meetings, voter education and that preparations for 
the elections can be fully guaranteed," Mr Niehaus said. 
  He added that a leadership summit to address the serious 
situation in Natal was now even more urgent than before and the 
ANC hoped it would be held as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

