<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Viljoen Doubts de Klerk Assurance on kwaZulu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Viljoen Doubts de Klerk Assurance on kwaZulu </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103144494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1427 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB3103144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by P Bulger] </F>
  [Text] Johannesburg March 31 SAPA -- Freedom Front leader 
Constand Viljoen said he doubted President F W de Klerk's 
assurance that kwaZulu would not suffer the same fate as 
Bophuthatswana, Ciskei, Lebowa and Qwaqwa, SABC radio news 
reported. 
  Gen Viljoen questioned the manner in which Mr de Klerk had 
declared the state of emergency in Natal/kwaZulu, saying he 
doubted denials that the African National Congress and National 
Party [NP] had not planned the emergency beforehand. He said he 
would consider inviting all parties, excluding the NP and ANC, 
to discuss whether the elections should be held in April. 
  CP leader Ferdi Hartzenberg also criticised the 
announcement. 
He said the intention was to overthrow the kwaZulu government 
and to compromise Zulu King Goodwill Zwelithini's authority. He 
said there could be no talk of a free and fair election under a 
state of emergency. 

</TEXT>

