<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Volksfront Condemns `One-Sided' Declaration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Volksfront Condemns `One-Sided' Declaration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103161094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1506 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB3103161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg March 31 SAPA -- The Afrikaner 
Volksfront [National Front, AVF] on Thursday [31 March] asked 
that the state of emergency in kwaZulu/Natal be lifted and the 
matter discussed with King Goodwill Zwelithini and Inkatha 
Freedom Party President Mangosuthu Buthelezi. An AVF statement 
condemned what it called, "the one-sided imposition of the state 
of emergency on kwaZulu/Natal by (State President) F W de Klerk 
on the instructions of the African National Congress". It said 
the state of emergency was an act of aggression against the Zulu 
nation and, in particular, the king and Mr Buthelezi. The state 
of emergency was also a sign that negotiations had failed. The 
election now needed to be postponed, the statement said. 

</TEXT>

