<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PAC Calls Natal State of Emergency `Tragic' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PAC Calls Natal State of Emergency `Tragic' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103150294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1443 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB3103150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg March 31 SAPA -- The decision to 
declare a state of emergency in kwaZulu/Natal was "politically 
wrong and tragic", the Pan Africanist Congress [PAC] said in a 
statement on Thursday [31 March]. A PAC spokesman said: "The 
Transitional Executive Council [TEC] has no control over the 
armed forces which remain in the control of the regime. This is 
a contradiction. We would have expected that control of the 
armed forces be given to the TEC". The organisation called for 
a special sitting of multiparty negotiators to reverse the TEC's 
decision and mandate an international peacekeeping force to 
normalise the situation in violence-torn areas. 

</TEXT>

