<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buthelezi Criticizes Visit by U.S. Congressmen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buthelezi Criticizes Visit by U.S. Congressmen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103130594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1256 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB3103130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Durban March 31 SAPA -- Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] 
President Mangosuthu Buthelezi on Thursday [31 March] 
critricised a group of visitng American congressmen for being 
misinformed about South Africa's political realities, SABC radio 
news reports. 
  The mainly Democrats delegation is led by United States 
Congressman John Lewis. They will end their tour on Friday in 
Cape Town 
  Mr Buthelezi said at a breakfast meeting he was grateful for 
past help, but asked the delegation to be more "even handed " in 
future. 
  Delegation members urged the IFP to reconsider taking part 
in 
the election at the meeting. They said they hoped South Africa 
would not degenerate into civil war. 
  Mr Buthelezi responded by saying the IFP would not support a 
"fatally flawed" constitution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

