<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commonwealth Unlikely To Send Peacekeeping Force </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commonwealth Unlikely To Send Peacekeeping Force </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3003165794 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 
1600 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3003165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Commonwealth says it is unlikely to send a 
peacekeeping force to South Africa if civil unrest escalates 
before and after next month's first all-race elections. 
Commonwealth Secretary General Emeka Anyaoku said the 
Commonwealth was not a peace-keeping organization. He said it 
was only acting as a mediator to help strengthen democracy in 
South Africa. The Commonwealth, a loose association of former 
British colonies, has sent a mission of observers to South 
Africa for the elections from the 26th to the 28th of next month. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

