<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   IEC Handling 385 Electoral Code Complaints </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IEC Handling 385 Electoral Code Complaints </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3003193994 Johannesburg THE STAR in English 30 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> MB3003193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg THE STAR </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Independent Electoral Commission [IEC] is now 
dealing with 385 complaints of electoral code breaches, and has 
issued 13 summonses to political parties. 
  Fifteen matters have been referred to mediation, while 50 
complaints files have been closed because they were frivolous or 
settled, investigations unit head Kgomotse Moroke said at an IEC 
briefing yesterday. 
  It was proving difficult to get statements from witnesses. 
  The directorate's head, Albert Mokwena, said voter education 
gaps has been identified among women in rural areas, the 
informal sector and public servants, particularly the army and 
police. 
  The IEC was penetrating kwaZulu by way of educating 
scholars, 
who in turn were educating families. 

</TEXT>

