<H3> <TI>   Portuguese Government Preparing Evacuation Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Portuguese Government Preparing Evacuation Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103144794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3103144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Portuguese Government is preparing an emergency 
plan to evacuate 600,000 Portuguese nationals from South Africa 
if the security situation deteriorates before or after the 
elections. Reports from Lisbon indicate that the returnees would 
be housed in disused buildings and military bases in northern 
Portugal after being airlifted from South Africa. Portuguese 
Prime Minister Anibal Cavaco Silva said he was extremely 
concerned about the violence in South Africa but that he did not 
think he should advise the Portuguese community in South Africa 
to leave the country yet. 

</TEXT>

