<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    People's Party Elects National Chairman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB3103174594 Monrovia Radio ELBC in English 0900 GMT 31 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> AB3103174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Monrovia Radio ELBC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Liberian People's Party [LPP] has elected Dr. 
Togbah-Nah Tipoteh as the national chairman of the party. At an 
emergency meeting of LPP's high decision-making organ, the 
organizing committee, Dr. Tipoteh was elected by acclamation. A 
release from the LPP's office says Dr. Tipoteh's [word 
indistinct] comes in the wake of the former chairman, Dr. 
Wolokollie's request to the organizing committee to find a 
full-time chairman to prepare the party adequately for the 
pending elections. The organizing committee, in the release, 
commended Mr. Wolokollie for the leadership provided the party 
in its most difficult period and hoped that in his new 
assignment as special liaison of the party with the LNTG 
[Liberian National Transitional Government], Mr. Wolokollie will 
exhibit equal commitment in the discharge of his duties. 
  Dr. Tipoteh, in his thanks to his solid partisans for his 
unanimous election, pledged continuity in the implementation of 
the general policies of the party. 
  Meanwhile, Dr. (Joseph Volloh) has been named chairman of 
the 
policy council of the party. He replaces Dr. Togba-Nah Tipoteh. 

</TEXT>

