mercenaries and others on the battle fronts. Recently the head 
of the South African Army said mercenaries operating in Angola 
did not do so with the government's consent. However, when 
UNITA killed 12 South African nationals, including a colonel, on 
22 March during clashes, Pretoria became agitated. 

