<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Frelimo Accuses Renamo of Violating Peace Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Frelimo Accuses Renamo of Violating Peace Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103144894 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1030 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3103144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The fourth session of the Central Committee of the 
Mozambique Liberation Front [Frelimo] was held in Matola 
recently. The final communique reflects the issues discussed at 
the meeting: 
  The Mozambican Government continues to strictly adhere to 
the 
General Peace Accord. Although the international community is 
assisting in the implementation of the General Peace Accord and 
in the democratization of the Mozambican society, Frelimo's 
Central Committee noted with apprehension the patronizing 
attitude that some members of the international community have 
shown toward Renamo on a number of occasions, as well as the 
actions aimed at downplaying the seriousness of the violations 
of the General Peace Accord, and underestimating Renamo's 
maneuvers to avoid fulfilling the agreed timetables. 
  In complete disregard of its public statements on the 
upholding of democracy and human rights, Renamo continues to 
prevent the access and movement of citizens in areas under its 
control, thereby violating the General Peace Accord. Moreover, 
Renamo prohibits economic activities -- namely, hunting, 
fishing, and logging in areas under its control in violation of 
the spirit and letter of the General Peace Accord and the 
Constitution of the Republic. 

</TEXT>

