<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Confinement of Troops to Assembly Areas Slows </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103200794 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1730 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3103200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The movement of government and Mozambique National 
Resistance [Renamo] forces to assembly areas has become 
increasingly slower over the past few days. Since the beginning 
of this week, only 68 government troops and four from Renamo 
arrived at assembly areas. A total of 33,369 soldiers from the 
government had been confined by yesterday. This represents 54 
percent of the total number of soldiers to be confined. On 
Renamo's side, a total of 14,809 soldiers have already been 
confined. This represents 77 percent of troops to be confined. 

</TEXT>

