<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Transvaal IFP: Civil War To Follow State of Emergency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Transvaal IFP: Civil War To Follow State of Emergency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103180794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 
1600 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3103180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  Afrikaans </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] in the Transvaal has 
threatened that civil war will follow the declaration of a state 
emergency in kwaZulu-Natal and the murder of eight hostel 
residents on the East Rand. The minibus taxi, in which the 
hostel dwellers were travelling, was ambushed near the kweSini 
Hostel in Katlehong and the occupants shot. According to one of 
the wounded, the attackers were apparently in police uniform. 

</TEXT>

