<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   KwaZulu Civil Servants Strike, Demand Pensions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KwaZulu Civil Servants Strike, Demand Pensions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103195594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1907 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB3103195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Durban March 31 SAPA -- Hundreds of kwaZulu civil 
servants in Umlazi near Durban have vowed not to return to work 
before the kwaZulu government addresses their demands for their 
pensions to be paid out, SABC [South African Broadcasting 
Corporation] radio news reported on Thursday [31 March]. The 
civil servants, some of them from places outside Umlazi, have 
been meeting at a stadium outside the township since the 
beginning of the week. 
  Meanwhile, the launch of an African National Congress 
election campaign for Umlazi pupils has been cancelled by the 
Congress of South African Students after school principals 
refused to allow the pupils to attend a meeting on Thursday. 
School principals are reported to have said that pupils were 
busy with their quarterly examinations. 

</TEXT>

