<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Reveals Support for ANC in PWV Shrinking </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Reveals Support for ANC in PWV Shrinking </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3103181894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3103181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to an opinion poll by the Institute for a 
Multiparty Democracy, the estimated support for the ANC in the 
PWV [Pretoria, Witwatersrand, Vereeniging] region has shrunk by 
almost 8 percent in the past three months, while the National 
Party [NP] has gained almost 3 percent. The poll shows that the 
ANC can now bargain on 38 percent support and the NP on 18. 
Sixteen percent of respondents have refused to say for whom 
they plan to vote, and 8 percent have not yet made up their 
minds. The poll has revealed that the situation in at least 
half of the black residential areas is such that voters are 
unable to make political choices without interference. A survey 
released in Natal yesterday showed that the ANC enjoyed 37 
percent support, Inkatha 18 percent, and the NP 14. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

