<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNITA Says Government Hindering Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNITA Says Government Hindering Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0104093394 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 0600 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0104093394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Union for the Total Independence of 
Angola [UNITA] yesterday complained to the UN Security Council 
that Luanda is hindering talks on national reconciliation in 
Lusaka. In a letter delivered by Ambassador Jardo Muecalia, 
UNITA's Representative in Washington, who left for New York 
yesterday, UNITA says that the Luanda government was adopting a 
line aimed at prolonging the talks so that they will fail. The 
same document states that Luanda is interested in the UN 
Security Council imposing further sanctions on UNITA, this being 
the main cause of its intransigence and arrogance in Lusaka. 

</TEXT>

