  [Text] Venancio de Moura, foreign affairs minister of the 
Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor Party, 
MPLA-PT, is currently visiting Lunda Sul Province. His call on 
the People's Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola, FAPLA, 
for become engaged in more fighting, has enraged the people. 
Reports say that the MPLA-PT foreign minister does not believe 
in the Lusaka peace talks. He showed similar spirit during the 
negotiations in Estoril, which led to the signing of the fragile 
Bicesse Accord. 
  A source in Lunda Sul Province said yesterday that Venancio 
de Moura's remarks in Saurimo are in line with the Luanda 
regime's warmongering plans for this year as announced by Jose 
Eduardo dos Santos in his New Year message. 

