<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   PCN Not To Contest Presidential Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PCN Not To Contest Presidential Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0104203294 Maputo NOTICIAS in Portuguese 26 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> MB0104203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo NOTICIAS </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Alvaro Machate, a member of the Collegiate 
Commission of the National Convention Party (PCN) and head of 
the party's administration department has told NOTICIAS that the 
PCN will not contest the presidential elections. He said the 
PCN will only contest the legislative elections. 
  He said opposition parties should unite to find a single 
presidential candidate because "we are about 16 officially 
registered parties, and if each one of us submits its candidate 
we will risk splitting the votes and encouraging war." [passage 
omitted] 
  Turning to the system of government that would eventually be 
in place in the country, he is for the "establishment of a 
government of national unity." He noted that "this country has 
gone through many years of war and people do not know each other 
well. Hence, it would be advisable for whoever wins the 
presidential election, not to consider only his party, but other 
people with potential, if he wants to guarantee peace." 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

