<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANC: Recommendations Not Binding </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANC: Recommendations Not Binding </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0404182594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0404182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The ANC says that recommendations made by 
international mediators in talks on possible amendments to the 
constitution will not be binding. An ANC official who did not 
want to be identified said the mediators would be here to 
mediate, not to arbitrate. The mediators, including two former 
foreign affairs ministers, Dr. Henry Kissinger of the United 
States and Britain's Lord Carrington, are due to arrive in South 
Africa this week. The ANC and IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] joint 
working committee, which is meeting in Kempton Park today to 
make final arrangements for international mediation, is expected 
to meet the mediators later this week to suggest amendments to 
the constitution. 

</TEXT>

