<H3> <TI>   ANC Concerned by Rumors of Anarchy After Election </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANC Concerned by Rumors of Anarchy After Election </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0504065394 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0504065394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The ANC has expressed concern about that it calls 
wild rumors about expected anarchy and violence after the 
election. ANC spokesman Carl Niehaus said that the rumors were 
triggering off a psychosis of fear. 
  Reports at the weekend said that many whites have been 
stockpiling non-perishable supplies in anticipation of trouble. 
The fears were reportedly spurred by the carnage in 
Johannesburg last week, and an anonymous panic list distributed 
to businesses warning about water supplies being cut off and 
power pylons blown up. 
  Mr. Niehaus said that the ANC did not believe that there 
would be more violence after the election and that there was no 
need for concern. 

</TEXT>

