<H3> <TI>   UN Envoy Concludes Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Envoy Concludes Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0504202994 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 
1600 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0504202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] United Nations Undersecretary General Ismat Kittani 
has stressed UN concern about Mozambique's troubled peace 
process during a week-long visit. During his visit, which ended 
today, Mr. Kittani urged more speed in the process leading to 
elections scheduled for October. Military demobilization is 
running well behind schedule. The UN Security Council deadline 
for the elections is October and the deadline for the 
peace-keeping mission November. Mr. Kittani met President 
Joaquim Chissano and Renamo [Mozambique National Resistance] 
leader Afonso Dhlakama and will report back to the Security 
Council on the country's progress toward peace. Renamo peace 
negotiator Raul Domingos said Mr. Kittani's visit had shown the 
UN secretary general's concern to see the peace process end well. 

</TEXT>

