<F P=102>   MB0704083294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0712 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0704083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by A. Thomson] </F>
  [Text] Durban April 7 SAPA -- Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] 
National Chairman Dr Frank Mdlalose on Thursday called on 
African National Congress President Nelson Mandela to distance 
himself from what he called inflammatory remarks by former 
president of the ANC Youth League, Peter Mokaba. An IFP 
statement said Mr Mokaba had called IFP president Mr Mangosuthu 
Buthelezi a "coward" and a "criminal" in remarks on radio on 
