<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Zimbabwe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Rules Out Door-to-Door Registration Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Rules Out Door-to-Door Registration Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0604155594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1331 GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0604155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Harare April 6 SAPA -- Home Affairs Minister Dumiso 
Dabengwa has ruled out door-to-door registering of Zimbabwean 
voters, saying the suggestion was not feasible, ZIANA national 
news agency reports. Several members of Parliament, including a 
senior Zimbabwe Government official, have suggested that the 
country should consider door-to-door registering so as to ensure 
that all eligible voters register and participate in Zimbabwe's 
forthcoming general elections. However, Mr Dabengwa shut the 
door on the suggestion saying the exercise would be far too 
costly. 

</TEXT>

