<H3> <TI>   Tells UK Paper of Assassination Attempts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tells UK Paper of Assassination Attempts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0804064994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0804064994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Inkatha Freedom Party leader Mangosuthu 
Buthelezi says he has information that hit squads were sent to 
assassinate him in recent weeks. Dr. Buthelezi is quoted in the 
British newspaper, THE DAILY STAR. In an exclusive interview, 
Dr. Buthelezi said members of the South African Communist Party 
who were also members of the ANC were guilty of the attempts. 
He told the newspaper that he had little hope that the talks 
with the state president, F.W. de Klerk, and ANC leader Nelson 
Mandela today would produce any result. 

</TEXT>

