  [Text] The ANC-aligned trade union, Popcru [Police and 
Prison's Civil Rights Union], has threatened to arrest members 
of the South African Police Union, SAPU, if they proceed with a 
planned strike to back their demand for higher salaries. SAPU 
is a mainly white trade union with about 20,000 members. The 
threat was made by the chairman of Popcru, Mr. Gregory Rockman, 
a former police officer. 

