<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kigali Erupts in Violence; Ministers Killed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kigali Erupts in Violence; Ministers Killed </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Guards Abduct Other Ministers </H4>

<F P=102> AB0704134494 Paris AFP in English 1310 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0704134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kigali, 7 Apr (AFP) -- Three Rwandan ministers and 
their three United Nations guards were taken captive Thursday [7 
April] by members of President Juvenal Habyarimana's 
Presidential Guard, a spokesman for the UN mission in Rwanda 
said. "We do not know whether these elements of the 
Presidential Guard were acting on their own initiative or 
following orders," the spokesman said. 
  The three members of the cabinet, all members of the 
opposition, were named as Faustin Rucogoza, Frederic 
Nzamurambaho and Landouald Ndasingwa, the Information, 
Agriculture and Labour Ministers. They were taken from their 
homes, some with relatives, the spokesman added. 

</TEXT>

