<H3> <TI>   Medecins Sans Frontieres Evacuating Belgian Staff </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Medecins Sans Frontieres Evacuating Belgian Staff </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1004122094 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1100 
GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels La Une Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Medecins Sans Frontieres has decided to evacuate all 
its Belgian staff now in Rwanda in light of the anti-Belgian 
feeling reigning in the country. Medecins Sans Frontieres 
officials said that the decision was made because of the 
evolution of the situation in Rwanda. The humanitarian 
organization added that, if circumstances allow, Belgian staff 
will be replaced by medical staff of other nationalities. 

</TEXT>

